personalInfo.splInterest: Watching movies, reading, Notre Dame football

tourBios.carHigh:
2013: Made the cut in just four of nine Web.com Tour starts. Best week was a T26 at the Cox Classic. Did not qualify for the Tour Finals.

2012: Had his two best outings of the season during the summer, finishing T7 at the Children's Invitational in late July and T14 at the News Sentinel Open in late August. 2011: Made the cut in eight of 25 starts and had a pair of top-10s during his rookie season on the Web.com Tour. Earned the first top-10 with a T7 at the Melwood Prince George's County Open. Closed with a 5-under 66 that featured a birdie-eagle finish...Fired an 8-under 63 in the third round of the Nationwide Children's Hospital Invitational and moved to within three strokes of the 54-hole leader. Finished T9 in Columbus. 2010: Played on the eGolf Tour. Made 15 starts, with a best finish of T7 at the Golf in Morocco Classic.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was an honorable mention All-American in 2008-2009 at Texas Christian University.
tourBios.personal: Has two brothers. Older brother, Tad, played golf at Indiana University...Lists Will Hutter as an instructor...Biggest thrill in golf is playing in five straight U.S. Amateurs...Biggest thrill outside golf is getting married...Favorite golf courses are Victoria National GC near Evansville, Ind., and Wolf Run GC. He would like to play Augusta National...Favorite teams are the Notre Dame Fighting Irish, the TCU Horned Frogs, the Dallas Cowboys and the Indianapolis Colts...Only drinks milk or water...Favorite TV show is "How I Met Your Mother," and "Pirates of the Caribbean" is his favorite movie...Peyton Manning and Tiger Woods are his favorite athletes to watch, and Eminem is his favorite entertainer...San Francisco is his favorite place to visit, and St. Lucia is his favorite vacation spot...Would have his dad and brothers in his dream foursome.
tourBios.otherInfo: Three-time all-state selection and state champion at Zionsville Community High School.

dyn.dynResults: He has finished 7th on the Web.com Tour 2 times.
